    {
      "title": "Avoir — present (j'ai faim)",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Say what you have — and how you feel",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 6,
      "explanation": "Avoir (to have): j'ai, tu as, il/elle a, nous avons, vous avez, ils/elles ont. French uses avoir where English uses 'to be' for states: avoir faim (be hungry), avoir soif (be thirsty), avoir vingt ans (be twenty), avoir raison (be right).",
      "culture_note": "Never say 'je suis vingt ans' — age is something you HAVE in French.",
      "references": [
