    {
      "title": "Il y a — there is / there are",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Say what exists or is available",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 10,
      "explanation": "Il y a covers both 'there is' and 'there are' — it never changes for plural: il y a un livre, il y a deux livres. Negative: il n'y a pas de… (no article, just de). Question: est-ce qu'il y a… ?",
